# Only fail `npm audit` (and CI) on high/critical severity findings.
#
# Why: Next.js bundles its own private copy of PostCSS (in
# node_modules/next/node_modules/postcss) for its internal build pipeline.
# npm flags this as a moderate vulnerability (GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93) even though:
#   1. The PostCSS XSS CVE is a build-time, not a runtime, issue.
#   2. Next's internal PostCSS only ever processes our own source files.
#   3. npm's only "fix" would downgrade Next.js to 9.3.3 — clearly wrong.
#   4. Every Next.js release through 16.x carries this same vendored copy.
#
# Our top-level postcss dependency is pinned to 8.5.10+ (patched).
# This setting keeps `npm audit` useful without crying wolf on an unfixable
# moderate in a third-party vendored dependency.
audit-level=high
